>From: George Lyle

> > 55 gallon barrel?

>Not a bad idea.  It has to be clean and uncoated inside.  Fill it with
>enough solution to submerge the wheel, and suspend the wheel from a 2x4
>across the top of the drum.  Hook the wheel to one side of the current
>source, the drum to the other side (which side is which I'll leave to an
>electrochem expert) and have at it.


Be careful of sparks. Combustable gases emit from the process(think 
Hindenberg). They disapate rapidly, but are still exiting the solution the 
entire time the setup is running.


- to the part
+ to the barrel

If doing the inside of a gas tank the connections would be reversed and the 
anode would be dropped into the tank, not touching the tank of course.



